  "texts": [
    "Despite the huge number of papers available, only those with experimentally observed transcriptional links are relevant to the extraction of relationships among biological entities.",
    "Further, only sections containing key sentences can be used for identifying biological interactions.",
    "These sentences reference multiple biological entities, and have complex structures comprising several clauses and technical terminology [4].",
    "Biological experiments are susceptible to errors during data collection, demanding substantial efforts to establish the relevance and authenticity of extracted regulations.",
    "Thus, most structured databases such as TRANSFAC [5] and Reg-ulonDB [6], rely on human experts to pre-process scientific papers, extract domain-related relations, and authenticate the information [7]."
